'''Kinnernet''' is a networking event for  experts, held at the Ohalo Resort in  annually each Spring since 2003. Organised by , founding investor of , Kinnernet serves as a think tank for the Internet, with some 250 professionals in the field meeting at each year's event, including many of the world's leading experts in the field. Previous attendees have included , , , , ,  and .
Much of what is discussed later becomes a topic at the  Marker, a two day Internet business conference in .
Kinnernet takes the form of an invitation-only "geek camp", modelling itself on Tim O'Reilly's . Kinnernet aims to provide like-minded individuals the opportunity to gather informally and discuss topics of mutual interest.